00036 /// configuration struct for diffs
00037 struct DiffConfig 
00038 {
00039     /// precision with which two doubles are compared
00040     double precision;
00041 
00042     /// ignore all file level metadata, and most scan level metadata,
00043     /// i.e. verify scan binary data, plus important scan metadata:
00044     ///  - msLevel 
00045     ///  - scanNumber 
00046     ///  - precursor.ionSelection
00047     bool ignoreMetadata;
00048 
00049     DiffConfig()
00050     :   precision(1e-6), 
00051         ignoreMetadata(false)
00052     {}
00053 };

00247 ///     
00248 /// Calculate diffs of objects in the MSData structure hierarchy.
00249 ///
00250 /// A diff between two objects a and b calculates the set differences
00251 /// a\b and b\a.
00252 ///
00253 /// The Diff struct acts as a functor, but also stores the 
00254 /// results of the diff calculation.  
00255 ///
00256 /// The bool conversion operator is provided to indicate whether 
00257 /// the two objects are different (either a\b or b\a is non-empty).
00258 ///
00259 /// object_type requirements:
00260 ///   object_type a;
00261 ///   a.empty();
00262 ///   diff(const object_type& a, const object_type& b, object_type& a_b, object_type& b_a);
00263 ///
00264 template <typename object_type>
00265 struct Diff
00266 {
00267     Diff(const DiffConfig& config = DiffConfig())
00268     :   config_(config)
00269     {}
00270 
00271     Diff(const object_type& a,
00272                const object_type& b,
00273                const DiffConfig& config = DiffConfig())
00274     :   config_(config)
00275     {
00276         diff_impl::diff(a, b, a_b, b_a, config_);
00277     }
00278 
00279     object_type a_b;
00280     object_type b_a;
00281 
00282     /// conversion to bool, with same semantics as *nix diff command:
00283     ///  true == different
00284     ///  false == not different
00285     operator bool() {return !(a_b.empty() && b_a.empty());}
00286 
00287     Diff& operator()(const object_type& a,
00288                            const object_type& b)
00289     {
00290         diff_impl::diff(a, b, a_b, b_a, config_);
00291         return *this;
00292     }
00293 
00294     private:
00295     DiffConfig config_;
00296 };

00369 ///
00370 /// stream insertion of Diff results
00371 ///
00372 template <typename object_type>
00373 std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& os, const Diff<object_type>& diff)
00374 {
00375     TextWriter write(os, 1);
00376 
00377     if (!diff.a_b.empty())
00378     {            
00379         os << "+\n";
00380         write(diff.a_b);
00381     }
00382 
00383     if (!diff.b_a.empty())
00384     {            
00385         os << "-\n";
00386         write(diff.b_a);
00387     }
00388 
00389     return os;
00390 }
